I never heard so loud a voice issue from such an empty heart.
It’s true what they say: “The empty vessel makes the greatest sound.” Bardolph and Nym had ten times more courage than this roaring stage villain, whose nails any Joe could cut with a wooden dagger, but they are both hanged.
So would this man if he had the nerve to steal anything bravely.
I have to stay with the servants, who are with our camp’s luggage.
We’re sitting ducks for the French, if they only knew it, for there is no one guarding it but boys.
